  <dashboards>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Behav'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97464' id='10' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='1268'>
            <zone h='97464' id='5' type-v2='layout-basic' w='97538' x='1231' y='1268'>
              <zone h='48732' id='8' name='Impact' w='97538' x='1231' y='1268'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='48732' id='11' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='50000'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>For urban residents (red), the relationship between working hours and sleep quality/day energy is almost negligible, as shown by the very small negative slope (-0.00955). The R² value (0.0004643) indicates almost no explanatory power, and the p-value (0.45289) suggests that the relationship is not statistically significant.The urban line remains relatively flat, indicating that working hours have little to no impact on sleep quality and energy levels.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>For rural residents (green), there is a slightly stronger negative relationship (-0.051386), meaning that as working hours increase, sleep quality/day energy tends to decrease more noticeably compared to urban areas. Although the R² value (0.0116917) is still low, the p-value (0.0080292) indicates that this relationship is statistically significant. The rural line shows a slight downward trend, indicating a decrease in sleep quality and daytime energy as working hours increase.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Overall:</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>The impact of working hours is minimal for urban residents but shows a small yet significant negative effect for rural residents.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
