                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>For rural residents (green), there is a slightly stronger negative relationship (-0.051386), meaning that as working hours increase, sleep quality/day energy tends to decrease more noticeably compared to urban areas. Although the R² value (0.0116917) is still low, the p-value (0.0080292) indicates that this relationship is statistically significant. The rural line shows a slight downward trend, indicating a decrease in sleep quality and daytime energy as working hours increase.</run>
