                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'><![CDATA[For urban residents (red), there is a negative relationship between phone use before sleep and sleep quality/day energy (-0.1547). The R² value (0.01837) is low, but the p-value (< 0.0001) indicates that the relationship is statistically significant. The urban line slopes slightly downward, showing that increased screen use reduces sleep quality and energy.]]></run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'><![CDATA[For rural residents (green), the negative relationship is stronger (-0.32768), showing a greater decline in sleep quality/day energy with increased phone use. The R² value (0.0799119) is still relatively low but higher than urban, and the p-value (< 0.0001) confirms that the relationship is statistically significant. The rural line shows a steeper downward trend, indicating a stronger negative impact.]]></run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Overall:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Screen use before sleep negatively affects both groups, with a stronger impact observed among rural residents.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{62E483F5-D319-4024-BC24-3759E20DA303}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Conclusion'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='97143' id='3' type-v2='text' w='89385' x='4615' y='2500'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>This study highlights the urban–rural lifestyle differences in Bhutan and their relationship with sleep quality and daytime energy. Based on 366 respondents, the findings show that urban residents are more engaged in mental and mixed types of work and tend to work slightly longer hours, while rural residents are more involved in physical work. However, differences in sleep duration and screen use between the two groups are relatively small, suggesting that lifestyles across urban and rural areas are becoming more similar.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>The analysis shows that working hours have minimal influence on sleep quality and daytime energy, especially in urban areas, while having a small but statistically significant effect in rural areas. In contrast, screen use before bedtime has a consistent negative impact on sleep quality and energy levels in both groups, with a stronger effect observed among rural residents. On the other hand, sleep duration is positively associated with better sleep quality and higher daytime energy, indicating that adequate sleep remains a key factor for overall well-being.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Although awareness of healthy sleep habits is already high among respondents such as reducing screen time, maintaining a consistent sleep schedule, and creating a stress-free environment, there is still a gap between knowledge and actual behavior. The strong willingness among participants to use a sleep-support mobile application further suggests an opportunity to support better sleep practices through digital tools and practical interventions.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Overall, the study emphasizes that sleep is not just a routine activity but an essential component of health, productivity, and quality of life. Promoting better sleep habits, reducing screen use before bedtime, and encouraging consistent routines can help individuals across both urban and rural communities improve their daily energy and long-term well-being.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
