                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>The analysis shows that working hours have minimal influence on sleep quality and daytime energy, especially in urban areas, while having a small but statistically significant effect in rural areas. In contrast, screen use before bedtime has a consistent negative impact on sleep quality and energy levels in both groups, with a stronger effect observed among rural residents. On the other hand, sleep duration is positively associated with better sleep quality and higher daytime energy, indicating that adequate sleep remains a key factor for overall well-being.</run>
