    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Problem &amp; purpose'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='860' maxwidth='650' minheight='560' minwidth='420' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='56974' id='5' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='97538' x='1231' y='41758'>
            <zone h='2853' id='7' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='41758'>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone forceUpdate='true' h='40490' id='10' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='1268'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Although studies in Bhutan and around the world show that lifestyle habits like work hours, screen use, and daily routines affect sleep and wellbeing, there is still limited understanding of how these factors impact sleep quality and daytime energy for urban and rural people in Bhutan. Urban residents often spend more time on screens, work longer hours, and spend more time sitting with less physical activity, while rural residents usually follow traditional routines, stay more active, and go to bed earlier.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>This raises the question: how do these rural–urban lifestyle differences in Bhutan such as work hours, screen use before sleep, and sleep patterns influence sleep quality and daytime energy levels?</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='26' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='84000' id='25' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='84000' x='8000' y='8000'>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='40490' id='10' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='1268'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Although studies in Bhutan and around the world show that lifestyle habits like work hours, screen use, and daily routines affect sleep and wellbeing, there is still limited understanding of how these factors impact sleep quality and daytime energy for urban and rural people in Bhutan. Urban residents often spend more time on screens, work longer hours, and spend more time sitting with less physical activity, while rural residents usually follow traditional routines, stay more active, and go to bed earlier.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>This raises the question: how do these rural–urban lifestyle differences in Bhutan such as work hours, screen use before sleep, and sleep patterns influence sleep quality and daytime energy levels?</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
                <zone h='2853' id='7' type-v2='text' w='97538' x='1231' y='41758'>
