    <dashboard name='Story 1' type='storyboard'>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-description'>
          <format attr='text-align' id='story-description_9' value='right' />
          <format attr='wrap' id='story-description_9' value='on' />
          <format attr='background-color' id='story-description_9' value='#ffffffd3' />
          <format attr='background-color' id='story-description_29' value='#ffffffd9' />
          <format attr='border-width' id='story-description_29' value='0' />
          <format attr='border-style' id='story-description_29' value='none' />
          <format attr='text-orientation' id='story-description_29' value='0' />
          <format attr='wrap' id='story-description_29' value='on' />
        </style-rule>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='184' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='964' maxwidth='1016' minheight='964' minwidth='1016' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98340' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='830'>
            <zone h='3423' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98426' x='787' y='830' />
            <zone fixed-size='149' h='15456' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98426' x='787' y='4253' />
            <zone h='79461' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98426' x='787' y='19709'>
              <flipboard active-id='36' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='Title' captured-sheet='Dashboard 19' id='36' />
                  <story-point caption='Introduction' captured-sheet='Dashboard 6' id='38'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <dashboard name='Dashboard 6'>
                        <zone id='10'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='14'>Urban-Rural lifestyle differences in Bhutan </run>
                            <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>I am Sonam Peldon, Gedu College of Business Studies intern and data practitioner at Data Scientists Pvt. Ltd., exploring how lifestyle habits affect health and wellbeing. This project is to examine how daily routines such as sleep, work, and screen use differ between urban and rural residents in Bhutan and how these differences influence sleep quality and daytime energy. Using these insights, I aim to develop evidence-based tools, like a website and mobile app, to help individuals and communities improve their daily habits and overall wellbeing</run>
                            <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Key Areas Covered:</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>1. Evidence of Lifestyle Impacts on Sleep and Wellbeing </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>2. Local Context </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>3. Purpose of the Study </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>4. Study Overview and Findings</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>5. Recommendations for Improving Sleep Health </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>6. Key Takeaways</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Evidence of Lifestyle Impacts on Sleep and Wellbeing' captured-sheet='study' id='30'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <dashboard name='study'>
                        <zone id='3'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial,sans-serif' fontsize='11'>There is strong evidence that lifestyle habits affect sleep and overall wellbeing. Studies in Bhutan and other populations show that sleep is closely linked to health. For example, research based on Bhutan’s Gross National Happiness survey found that people who sleep too little (6 hours or less) or too much (11 hours or more) are more likely to report poor health. This suggests that both insufficient and excessive sleep can negatively affect wellbeing (Sithey et al., 2017).</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial,sans-serif' fontsize='11'>Sleep quality is also an important factor in mental health. A study among people with epilepsy in Bhutan found that individuals with poor sleep were more likely to experience depression and social isolation. This indicates that disturbed sleep affects not only physical health but also emotional and psychological wellbeing (Stauder et al., 2020). Similar findings are seen among older adults, where sleep problems such as insomnia are associated with lower quality of life, especially when combined with other conditions like pain and depression (Dorji et al., 2018).</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial,sans-serif' fontsize='11'>Work and daily routines further influence sleep and wellbeing. Research on nurses in Bhutan shows that those who are able to rest properly, such as by taking naps during night shifts, experience less fatigue and perform better at work (Gyeltshen et al., 2023). In contrast, studies on workers in Thimphu indicate that high workload and job stress are common and can negatively impact mental wellbeing (Naveed et al., 2020).</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial,sans-serif' fontsize='11'>In addition, modern lifestyle habits such as screen use are increasingly affecting sleep. Studies among young adults show that spending long hours on smartphones, especially before bedtime, is linked to poor sleep quality and increased daytime tiredness. Higher screen use is consistently associated with more sleep disturbances and lower energy levels (Deivendran et al., 2025).</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial,sans-serif' fontsize='11'>Overall, a clear pattern emerges from these studies that unhealthy lifestyle habits such as irregular sleep, high stress, and excessive screen time lead to poor sleep and reduced wellbeing. These findings are also reflected in everyday life, where individuals who maintain healthy routines and good sleep habits tend to feel more energetic, focused, and mentally stable.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption=' Local Context, and               Purpose of the Study' captured-sheet='Problem &amp; purpose' id='19'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <dashboard name='Problem &amp; purpose'>
                        <zone id='10'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Although previous studies in Bhutan and globally show that lifestyle habits such as work hours, screen use, and daily routines affect sleep and wellbeing, there is limited evidence on how these factors specifically influence sleep quality and daytime energy among urban and rural residents in Bhutan. Urban populations tend to spend more time on screens, work longer hours, and have more sedentary lifestyles, while rural residents generally follow traditional routines, remain more active, and go to bed earlier. </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Despite these differences, it is not well understood how these rural–urban lifestyle patterns relate to sleep health and daily functioning. Addressing this gap, the present study examines rural–urban lifestyle differences in Bhutan. It compares Bhutanese lifestyles by focusing on average work hours, screen use before sleep, and sleep patterns, and how these factors influence sleep quality and daytime energy levels.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Study Overview and Findings' captured-sheet='Purpose' id='32'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <dashboard name='Purpose'>
                        <zone id='3'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Study Purpose:</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'> Conducted an online survey during internship to understand lifestyle habits such as work , screen use, and sleep patterns among urban and rural residents in Bhutan.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Sample Size:</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'> 366 respondents participated</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Findings are structured into key areas:</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>1. Respondent Distribution</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Context and characteristics of the sample.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>2. Core Insights</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Differences between urban and rural populations in average work hours, screen use before bedtime, and sleep duration.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>3. Correlation Insights</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>How work hours, screen time, and sleep duration relate to sleep quality and daytime energy levels.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>4. Habits Affecting Sleep Quality</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Behaviors that improve helps to improve sleep.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>5. Preferences for Sleep Support Tools</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Æ </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Features respondents would like in digital tools.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>6. Future Interest in Sleep Tools</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Willingness to use digital support for better sleep.</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>7. Key Takeaways</run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Main patterns and trends identified from the survey.</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='1. Respondent Distribution' captured-sheet='Demographics (2)' id='33' />
                  <story-point caption='Work types' captured-sheet='core' id='21'>
                    <currentDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='Work types'>
                        <selection-collection>
                          <node-selection select-tuples='false'>
                            <oriented-node-reference orientation='horizontal'>
                              <node-reference>
                                <fields>
                                  <field>[federated.0smbf4a1a4zj2r1foztoz18bo7h6].[none:Calculation_1182844296785924:nk]</field>
                                </fields>
                                <multibucket>
                                  <bucket>&quot;Both&quot;</bucket>
                                </multibucket>
                              </node-reference>
                              <page-reference />
                            </oriented-node-reference>
                          </node-selection>
                        </selection-collection>
                      </worksheet>
                      <dashboard name='core'>
                        <zone id='38'>
                          <formatted-text>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Physical work is more common among rural residents, with 40 people involved compared to 60 in urban areas, showing only a small difference. </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>In contrast, mental work is more common among urban residents, with 69 people compared to 35 in rural areas. </run>
                            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='11'>Mixed work, which includes both physical and mental tasks, is much higher in urban areas, with 134 people, while only 40 rural residents fall into this category.</run>
                          </formatted-text>
                        </zone>
                      </dashboard>
                    </currentDeltas>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='Work types'>
                        <selection-collection>
                          <node-selection select-tuples='false'>
                            <oriented-node-reference orientation='horizontal'>
                              <node-reference>
                                <fields>
                                  <field>[federated.0smbf4a1a4zj2r1foztoz18bo7h6].[none:Calculation_1182844296785924:nk]</field>
                                </fields>
                                <multibucket>
                                  <bucket>&quot;Both&quot;</bucket>
                                </multibucket>
                              </node-reference>
                              <page-reference />
                            </oriented-node-reference>
                          </node-selection>
                        </selection-collection>
                      </worksheet>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='2. Core insights                                 2.1 Average work hours' captured-sheet='core work' id='34'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='Average work hours'>
                        <selection-collection />
                      </worksheet>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='2.2 Average screen use  ' captured-sheet='core (2)' id='22' />
                  <story-point caption='2.3 Average sleep hours' captured-sheet='core (3)' id='23' />
                  <story-point caption='3. Correlation Insights         3.1 Average Working Hours and Sleep quality and day energy level ' captured-sheet='Behav' id='24' />
                  <story-point caption='3.2 Average Screenuse Hours and Sleep quality and day energy level ' captured-sheet='Behav (2)' id='25' />
                  <story-point caption='3.3 Average Sleep Hours and Sleep quality and day energy level ' captured-sheet='Behav (3)' id='26' />
                  <story-point caption='4. Habits That Influence Sleep Quality' captured-sheet='Improvement' id='11'>
